The Borrower shall, and shall cause EG and the NBG to, ensure that the Projectis carried out in accordance with the Environmental and Social Standards, and implemented in accordance with the Environmental andSocial Commitment Plan (“ESCP”), all in a manner acceptable to the Bank.

Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV. The Borrower shall ensure that EG, not later than ninety (90) days after the EffectiveDate, has introduced a module within its existing accounting system for Project accounting and reporting, in a manner satisfactoryto the Bank.

title.narrative: Institutional actions to strengthen the partial credit guarantees program

baseline.value: EG currently does not have a monitoring system, a risk management framework, and an outreach strategy to evaluate the performanceand risks of the program and propose improvements in its design.

target.value: EG has strengthened the design and implementation arrangements of the program, including more robust risk monitoring, awarenesscampaigns, stronger participation agreements with PFIs, and financial modelling tool.

title.narrative: Institutional actions to strengthen the grants program

baseline.value: EG does not have an effective M&E system that allows the frequent review of the performance and outcomes of its grants program,which would provide evidence and technical grounds for improvements in the program.

target.value: EG has adopted a robust M&E framework and used evidence to improve the design of its grants program and develop sustainable optionsfor its development.

title.narrative: Institutional actions to strengthen the co-financing of interest payments program

baseline.value: EG does not have evaluation systems and measures in place to assess the effectiveness of its co-financing of interest payments onan frequent basis and better align its targeting towards strategic sectors and/or thematic areas.

target.value: EG has adopted a robust M&E framework and conducted an evaluation of its co-financing program, using evidence to propose amendmentsto improve targeting, eligibility criteria and other aspects of the program.
